A Clarkston charity shop is hoping to score with an auction of a signed Scotland shirt.A Scotland football shirt signed by Scotland and Rangers legend Colin Stein has been donated to Shelter Scotland's shop at Clarkston Toll, and will be auctioned off to raise vital funds for the housing and homelessness charity.The retro shirt, of the kind worn by the Scotland team in the late 1960s and early 1970s, was anonymously donated to the charity shop recently and is signed by Colin Stein, who scored nine goals for Scotland in 21 appearances.Stein was also part of the Rangers team that won the 1971-72 UEFA Cup Winners' Cup, scoring one of the three goals that brought the Glasgow side victory.